      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Decimal conventions:</strong> This tool uses common networking/SI units (1 Mbps = 1,000,000 bits/s). Some systems also use binary units (MiB, GiB), which can display different numbers.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Real-world overhead:</strong> Actual download/upload speeds can be lower than theoretical conversions due to protocol overhead, Wi-Fi quality, routing, congestion, server limits, and device performance.
